Cook rice as directed on package. Meanwhile, heat large nonstick skillet on high heat. Add chops; cook 2 min. or until bottoms of chops are browned. Reduce heat to medium; turn chops. Sprinkle with oregano; top with peppers, dressing and tomatoes. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 12 min. or until chops are cooked through (160F). Spoon rice onto serving plates; top with chops. Cover to keep warm. Increase heat under skillet to high; cook vegetable mixture 1 to 2 min. or until vegetables are tender and sauce is thickened, stirring occasionally. Spoon over chops; top with cheese.